Who the fuck are you people?

10
00:00:36.870 --> 00:00:38.747
[panting]

11
00:00:38.830 --> 00:00:40.040
[stammers]

12
00:00:47.005 --> 00:00:48.757
[kidnapper] You went to see Liv Cross.

13
00:00:49.925 --> 00:00:52.219
We're not just watching you.
we're watching everyone.

14
00:00:52.302 --> 00:00:53.345
[Coop panting]

15
00:00:53.428 --> 00:00:55.347
The money stays where it is.

16
00:00:57.224 --> 00:00:58.767
Understood?

17
00:00:58.851 --> 00:01:01.770
[breathes shakily] Yeah. Yeah.

18
00:01:04.188 --> 00:01:06.525
Fuck. [breathes heavily]

19
00:01:08.443 --> 00:01:10.696
[grunting. breathing heavily]

20
00:01:13.156 --> 00:01:15.075
[panting]

21
00:01:15.158 --> 00:01:16.535
[knife clatters]

22
00:01:20.330 --> 00:01:23.375
[gate opening]

23
00:01:28.297 --> 00:01:30.674
[engine starts. revs]

24
00:01:38.473 --> 00:01:41.059
[grunts. pants]

25
00:01:42.019 --> 00:01:43.437
[knife clatters]

26
00:01:54.323 --> 00:01:57.326
Fuck. [breathes heavily]

27
00:01:57.409 --> 00:01:59.036
[tense music playing]

28
00:02:26.480 --> 00:02:28.524
[panting]

29
00:02:36.782 --> 00:02:38.075
[retches]

30
00:02:38.158 --> 00:02:40.452
[sinister music playing]

31
00:02:47.501 --> 00:02:49.044
[exhales heavily]

32
00:03:07.020 --> 00:03:08.438
[exhales deeply]

33
00:03:23.579 --> 00:03:24.580
[sighs]

34
00:03:29.668 --> 00:03:30.669
[sighs]

35
00:03:30.752 --> 00:03:33.130
[theme song playing]

36
00:04:50.624 --> 00:04:51.625
[sniffles]

37
00:04:56.046 --> 00:04:57.047
[sniffles]

38
00:05:00.175 --> 00:05:01.343
[sniffles]

39
00:05:09.977 --> 00:05:11.061
[Brie] Arlo!

40
00:05:11.144 --> 00:05:12.688
[Mel gasps. screams]

41
00:05:14.231 --> 00:05:15.315
[Brie] Arlo. buddy?

42
00:05:15.399 --> 00:05:18.277
- [Clay] Come on. bud. Come on home.
- [clapping]

43
00:05:18.360 --> 00:05:20.404
- [Brie] Arlo?
- [breathes heavily]

44
00:05:20.487 --> 00:05:21.488
[Brie] Arlo.

45
00:05:22.531 --> 00:05:24.867
- Arlo.
- [Clay whistling]

46
00:05:25.701 --> 00:05:27.911
- [Brie] Arlo.
- [Clay] Hey. Come home.

47
00:05:29.705 --> 00:05:30.706
[Brie] Arlo!

48
00:05:32.541 --> 00:05:34.585
- [Clay] Come on. Come on. Arlo.
- [Brie] Arlo.

49
00:05:35.627 --> 00:05:36.628
[Mel] Hey. Brie!

50
00:05:36.712 --> 00:05:39.715
[Clay] I don't know.
Probably around here somewhere.

51
00:05:39.798 --> 00:05:40.883
[Mel] Brie!

52
00:05:40.966 --> 00:05:43.719
- [Brie] Arlo. buddy. [kisses]
- [Clay whistles]

53
00:05:43.802 --> 00:05:47.472
- [Brie] Arlo. Arlo. come on out. buddy.
- [Clay] Come home. buddy. [kisses]

54
00:05:47.556 --> 00:05:48.724
[Brie] Arlo.

55
00:05:48.807 --> 00:05:51.435
[Clay whistling] Come home. bud.

56
00:05:51.518 --> 00:05:53.353
- [Brie] Arlo.
- [Clay] Come home.

57
00:05:53.437 --> 00:05:54.938
[pants] Hey.

58
00:05:55.564 --> 00:05:57.399
- [Clay] Where are you at. buddy?
- [Brie] Arlo.

59
00:05:57.482 --> 00:05:58.609
[Clay] Come on. Arlo.

60
00:05:58.692 --> 00:06:00.986
- [Brie] Arlo.
- [Clay] Buddy. come on.

61
00:06:01.069 --> 00:06:02.112
Arlo.

62
00:06:04.907 --> 00:06:05.908
[sighs]

63
00:06:07.826 --> 00:06:08.827
Come on.

64
00:06:11.038 --> 00:06:12.039
[sighs]

65
00:06:13.207 --> 00:06:14.917
[grunts] Come on. kiddo.

66
00:06:19.421 --> 00:06:22.132
- Look at this. Really?
- [chuckles]

67
00:06:26.637 --> 00:06:28.180
- Hey.
- Hey. Mom.

68
00:06:32.726 --> 00:06:33.936
Are you back?

69
00:06:34.770 --> 00:06:36.271
Let's not make a big deal about it. okay?

70
00:06:36.355 --> 00:06:38.148
Does this mean
you're reconsidering Princeton?

71
00:06:39.107 --> 00:06:43.028
- [sighs]
- [stammers] Just a joke. How about Yale?

72
00:06:46.240 --> 00:06:47.241
No?

73
00:06:48.242 --> 00:06:49.284
Cut your losses.

74
00:06:50.661 --> 00:06:51.870
- Thank you.
- Don't mention it.

75
00:06:59.086 --> 00:07:00.087
You okay?

76
00:07:00.170 --> 00:07:01.171
Yeah.

77
00:07:03.507 --> 00:07:05.384
- Rough night.
- [groans] Me too.

78
00:07:06.677 --> 00:07:08.679
- Yeah?
- [sighing]

79
00:07:13.725 --> 00:07:14.726
You wanna come in?

80
00:07:15.686 --> 00:07:17.437
[Coop] Some questions
aren't just questions.

81
00:07:17.521 --> 00:07:19.189
they're portals to another world.

82
00:07:19.982 --> 00:07:22.568
It was a world I would've given
anything to return to.

83
00:07:22.651 --> 00:07:24.444
But I was in trouble.

84
00:07:24.528 --> 00:07:27.072
and this was the last place
I wanted to bring that trouble to.

85
00:07:27.155 --> 00:07:28.740
I should probably get going.

86
00:07:28.824 --> 00:07:30.909
[tender music playing]

87
00:07:45.799 --> 00:07:46.800
[grunts]

88
00:07:46.884 --> 00:07:48.093
[inhales sharply]

89
00:07:48.177 --> 00:07:49.511
[in Korean] Fine.

90
00:07:49.595 --> 00:07:51.513
If that's what you think is best.

91
00:07:52.347 --> 00:07:53.348
Hmm.

92
00:07:54.433 --> 00:07:56.185
[in English] God. [sighs]

93
00:07:56.268 --> 00:07:58.270
I never should've involved my mother
in this party.

94
00:07:59.313 --> 00:08:01.106
Can you please stop talking
about a baby shower

95
00:08:01.190 --> 00:08:03.400
when a doctor is about to take
a scalpel to my manhood?

96
00:08:03.483 --> 00:08:05.068
[Grace] It's a sprinkle. not a shower.

97
00:08:05.152 --> 00:08:07.362
A distinction without a difference.

98
00:08:07.446 --> 00:08:09.489
And I didn't tell you
to schedule your vasectomy now.

99
00:08:10.199 --> 00:08:12.743
It's not like you can
get me pregnant while I'm pregnant.

100
00:08:12.826 --> 00:08:14.036
With our luck? You don't know that.

101
00:08:14.119 --> 00:08:15.412
[knocks on door]

102
00:08:16.580 --> 00:08:17.664
- Barney…
- [Barney] Hey. Doc.

103
00:08:17.748 --> 00:08:19.666
- [Grace] Hi.
- …Grace. good morning.

104
00:08:19.750 --> 00:08:20.918
How we feeling?

105
00:08:21.001 --> 00:08:23.629
- [sighs. inhales sharply]
- Um. squeamish.

106
00:08:23.712 --> 00:08:26.048
- There's nothing to be concerned about.
- [laughs]

107
00:08:26.131 --> 00:08:29.176
It's a very simple procedure
with a quick recovery.

108
00:08:29.259 --> 00:08:30.969
You'll need to take it easy
for a couple weeks.

109
00:08:31.053 --> 00:08:33.304
but otherwise ice and Advil
should take care

110
00:08:33.388 --> 00:08:35.057
of any discomfort or swelling.

111
00:08:37.183 --> 00:08:40.229
You're going to castrate me
and not even let me enjoy the recovery?

112
00:08:41.104 --> 00:08:42.188
I'll call in some Percocet.

113
00:08:42.272 --> 00:08:45.400
Maybe some Demerol. too?
That stuff really agrees with me.

114
00:08:45.484 --> 00:08:49.530
He had a kidney stone a few years back.
Still talks about it.

115
00:08:49.613 --> 00:08:51.281
They say it's as painful as childbirth.

116
00:08:51.365 --> 00:08:53.700
You know what else is
as painful as childbirth?

117
00:08:54.618 --> 00:08:55.744
Childbirth.

118
00:08:57.996 --> 00:08:59.373
Percocet's just fine.

119
00:09:00.165 --> 00:09:03.043
Three bedrooms. two-and-a-half baths.

120
00:09:03.126 --> 00:09:07.172
a recently redone deck.
and they even finished the basement.

121
00:09:07.256 --> 00:09:10.133
- When was it built?
- [clicks tongue] 1993.

122
00:09:10.759 --> 00:09:11.760
So. it has character.

123
00:09:11.844 --> 00:09:13.679
Yeah. For Long Island.

124
00:09:13.762 --> 00:09:15.013
[Realtor chuckles] Sure.

125
00:09:15.597 --> 00:09:17.224
Are you relocating for work?

126
00:09:17.307 --> 00:09:18.600
Uh. not exactly.

127
00:09:19.977 --> 00:09:23.188
Husband. or… Oh. never mind. No ring.

128
00:09:23.272 --> 00:09:24.731
Very observant. Becca.

129
00:09:26.441 --> 00:09:28.193
[Becca] It's a dumb default question.

130
00:09:29.403 --> 00:09:32.781
Between us. my least favorite part
of the job is making my clients write

131
00:09:32.865 --> 00:09:34.908
"a single woman"
on their escrow documents.

132
00:09:36.034 --> 00:09:39.121
I mean. you're already wiring away
your entire net worth… [chuckles]

133
00:09:39.204 --> 00:09:41.874
…why not just throw in a splash
of indignity?

134
00:09:42.958 --> 00:09:45.502
And as for the kids. if private school
is important to you--

135
00:09:45.586 --> 00:09:48.547
Oh. no. no. no. Public school is fine.
I like this island.

136
00:09:49.381 --> 00:09:52.050
[Becca] It's a cultured marble.
like the backsplash.

137
00:09:52.134 --> 00:09:53.468
I mean. I went to public school.

138
00:09:53.552 --> 00:09:55.971
Although. I guess that doesn't exactly
support the argument.

139
00:09:56.054 --> 00:09:58.724
since I didn't even bother
applying to colleges.

140
00:09:58.807 --> 00:10:01.977
The extra room upstairs.
that could work well as a playroom.

141
00:10:02.060 --> 00:10:03.604
Or an office.

142
00:10:03.687 --> 00:10:05.105
Yeah. I don't hate that.

143
00:10:06.815 --> 00:10:08.358
You'd think my parents
would've intervened.

144
00:10:08.442 --> 00:10:12.529
They're ruthlessly pragmatic
about everything. except me. I guess.

145
00:10:13.363 --> 00:10:14.364
Only child.

146
00:10:15.908 --> 00:10:17.284
I wonder if they regret it.

147
00:10:18.076 --> 00:10:21.622
You know. making me think
I can be anything. do anything.

148
00:10:22.915 --> 00:10:25.501
I mean. at some point you have to wake up
and realize that. you know.

149
00:10:26.793 --> 00:10:28.420
you're not so special after all.

150
00:10:28.504 --> 00:10:30.631
["Captain Jack" playing]

151
00:10:35.761 --> 00:10:40.974
♪ Saturday night and you're still
Hanging around ♪

152
00:10:42.434 --> 00:10:47.397
♪ Tired of living in your one horse town ♪

153
00:10:49.566 --> 00:10:53.195
Hey. Sorry. um. wasn't Ali Cooper
supposed to be playing tonight?

154
00:10:53.278 --> 00:10:55.155
Ali's taking some time off.
Death in the family.

155
00:10:56.240 --> 00:10:59.034
[sighs] Okay.
Any idea when she might be back?

156
00:10:59.868 --> 00:11:00.869
She didn't say.

157
00:11:04.289 --> 00:11:06.333
- So. do you want something to drink?
- Uh. yeah. sure.

158
00:11:06.416 --> 00:11:08.669
- Uh. couldn't hurt. Whatever's on tap.
- [slams payment on table]

159
00:11:08.752 --> 00:11:14.508
♪ And you stare at the junkies
And the closet queens ♪

160
00:11:14.591 --> 00:11:15.592
[sighs]

161
00:11:16.635 --> 00:11:20.639
- [phone beeps]
- Hey. it's Ali. Mmm. yeah. just text me.

162
00:11:21.223 --> 00:11:25.519
Ali. hey. Please pick up.
Um. I need to talk to you.

163
00:11:25.602 --> 00:11:28.647
There's a lot going on over here.
Just call me back. Thanks.

164
00:11:28.730 --> 00:11:32.401
♪ But Captain Jack will get you
High tonight ♪

165
00:11:34.778 --> 00:11:38.282
♪ And take you to your special island ♪

166
00:11:40.868 --> 00:11:44.371
♪ Captain Jack will get you by tonight ♪

167
00:11:46.582 --> 00:11:50.502
♪ Just a little push
And you'll be smiling ♪

168
00:11:52.963 --> 00:11:54.464
[buzzing]

169
00:11:57.551 --> 00:11:59.636
Coop. this a surprise.

170
00:11:59.720 --> 00:12:02.598
Hey. Sam. Sorry to call so late.
but I need a favor.

171
00:12:03.599 --> 00:12:05.142
My curiosity is piqued.

172
00:12:05.225 --> 00:12:09.479
[sighs] Can you find out if anybody rented
an apartment to Ali recently?

173
00:12:10.355 --> 00:12:11.356
Is she okay?

174
00:12:12.608 --> 00:12:13.692
I don't know.

175
00:12:14.234 --> 00:12:16.486
She got some cash from my dad's estate.

176
00:12:16.570 --> 00:12:19.448
but I don't think she could swing
more than 3K a month.

177
00:12:20.157 --> 00:12:22.618
It's a small apartment market.
We'll find her.

178
00:12:24.077 --> 00:12:25.120
Thanks.

179
00:12:25.204 --> 00:12:26.496
Course.

180
00:12:26.580 --> 00:12:29.082
It's sweet how much you care about her.

181
00:12:29.166 --> 00:12:31.335
Yeah. well. maybe one day she'll think so.

182
00:12:31.418 --> 00:12:35.672
[laughs] I'm learning it's a fine line
between caring and suffocating.

183
00:12:37.132 --> 00:12:39.384
Are we gonna start talking about him now?

184
00:12:39.468 --> 00:12:41.053
[sighs] Definitely not.

185
00:12:41.637 --> 00:12:42.930
Whew.

186
00:12:43.013 --> 00:12:45.682
[sighs] Good night. Coop.

187
00:12:48.310 --> 00:12:50.187
[gentle music playing]

188
00:12:57.444 --> 00:13:00.906
[inhales deeply. sighs]

189
00:13:05.410 --> 00:13:06.954
[sighs]

190
00:13:08.205 --> 00:13:09.331
[engine starts]

191
00:13:20.217 --> 00:13:22.511
- [Grace] Hello. [laughs]
- [Maggie] Hi. [laughs]

192
00:13:22.594 --> 00:13:24.471
- Congratulations again.
- Good to see you.

193
00:13:24.555 --> 00:13:26.181
- Aw. and this is for you.
- Thank you.

194
00:13:26.265 --> 00:13:28.267
[gasps] I said no gifts.

195
00:13:28.350 --> 00:13:29.560
- Nobody believed you. babe.
- [scoffs]

196
00:13:29.643 --> 00:13:31.812
Yes. but I want credit for the gesture.

197
00:13:31.895 --> 00:13:34.022
- You can have it. [laughs]
- [both laughing]

198
00:13:34.106 --> 00:13:35.899
Okay. come on. Everyone's playing a game.

199
00:13:35.983 --> 00:13:37.192
Okay.

200
00:13:38.026 --> 00:13:39.987
All right. Look who finally made it.

201
00:13:40.070 --> 00:13:42.489
[all] Hey!

202
00:13:42.573 --> 00:13:44.491
- Hi. How are you?
- That's my cousin over there.

203
00:13:44.575 --> 00:13:48.829
Okay. focus. Boobs or baby butts?

204
00:13:48.912 --> 00:13:52.207
I would know those tits anywhere. Yeah.

205
00:13:52.291 --> 00:13:55.752
[laughs] I let her feel me up
that one time on a Miraval retreat.

206
00:13:55.836 --> 00:13:58.338
[Kat laughs] Don't underestimate
small boob privilege.

207
00:13:58.422 --> 00:14:01.175
Especially at our age.
Gravity comes for us all eventually.

208
00:14:01.258 --> 00:14:02.259
[all laugh]

209
00:14:02.342 --> 00:14:04.803
I will never know what it's like
to not have to wear a bra.

210
00:14:04.887 --> 00:14:05.971
Nobody feels sorry for you.

211
00:14:06.054 --> 00:14:07.222
[all laugh]

212
00:14:07.306 --> 00:14:09.850
It's so nice to see you two
getting along again.

213
00:14:09.933 --> 00:14:12.311
[groans] You have no idea how
uncomfortable that whole situation was.

214
00:14:12.394 --> 00:14:14.438
All that tiptoeing around.
it was exhausting.

215
00:14:14.521 --> 00:14:17.524
Well. don't make it all about you. Suz.
It was hard on me too.

216
00:14:17.608 --> 00:14:19.026
[all laugh]

217
00:14:21.486 --> 00:14:23.989
[Julie] Okay. everybody. focus.

218
00:14:24.072 --> 00:14:25.949
[Samantha] Oh. wait. no.
I already nailed it.

219
00:14:26.033 --> 00:14:27.034
- [Julie] You did?
- Uh. yeah.

220
00:14:27.117 --> 00:14:29.203
'Cause the boobs have space
on the top and the bottom.

221
00:14:29.286 --> 00:14:32.080
- And the butts are just. like. one line.
- Just turn the card upside down.

222
00:14:32.164 --> 00:14:33.457
- Hey.
- [gasps]

223
00:14:33.540 --> 00:14:35.709
- [laughs]
- Hey. You having fun?

224
00:14:35.792 --> 00:14:38.504
Um. I'm feeling kinda old for all this.

225
00:14:38.587 --> 00:14:39.880
Oh.

226
00:14:41.215 --> 00:14:42.674
So. what's your excuse?

227
00:14:43.342 --> 00:14:46.094
- What?
- You seem… out of it.

228
00:14:48.263 --> 00:14:49.640
I'm sorry.

229
00:14:49.723 --> 00:14:51.016
It's just. um…

230
00:14:53.185 --> 00:14:55.062
it's been a roller coaster with Tori.

231
00:14:55.145 --> 00:14:56.855
Oh. Yeah. I know.

232
00:14:58.023 --> 00:14:59.358
But is that it?

233
00:15:00.943 --> 00:15:02.319
[tires screech]

234
00:15:02.402 --> 00:15:06.073
Yeah. I'm having trouble writing.

235
00:15:06.156 --> 00:15:08.951
- Brain fog. Oh. excuse me.
- [server] Oh. thank you.

236
00:15:09.034 --> 00:15:11.078
But I'm starting
hormone replacement therapy.

237
00:15:11.161 --> 00:15:13.413
[gasps] Oh. thank God. Good for you.

238
00:15:13.497 --> 00:15:15.374
- Grace. come back. Come back.
- I'm… Sorry. [chuckles]

239
00:15:15.457 --> 00:15:16.542
We can't do this without you.

240
00:15:16.625 --> 00:15:18.710
[chuckles] Let's have lunch soon.

241
00:15:18.794 --> 00:15:21.296
so I can. you know.
watch you get drunk or something.

242
00:15:21.380 --> 00:15:22.798
- Say when.
- [laughs]

243
00:15:22.881 --> 00:15:25.050
[Gordy] This is what you
get up to unsupervised.

244
00:15:25.133 --> 00:15:27.052
You look at pictures
of each other's asses?

245
00:15:27.135 --> 00:15:29.680
- I've been missing out.
- [laughs] Yeah. you want in?

246
00:15:30.305 --> 00:15:32.391
- Oh. so many responses come to mind.
- [laughs]

247
00:15:33.308 --> 00:15:34.518
- You.
- Yeah?

248
00:15:34.601 --> 00:15:36.228
- Go away.
- [laughs]

249
