443
00:24:56.163 --> 00:24:59.082
- Mmm.
- Thanks again for bringing Tori home.

444
00:24:59.750 --> 00:25:02.544
Oh. come on. I told you she would
inevitably come to her senses

445
00:25:02.628 --> 00:25:04.338
and realize which parent she needed more.

446
00:25:04.421 --> 00:25:05.923
- Oh. hey.
- [sighs]

447
00:25:06.006 --> 00:25:09.134
Just add it to the ever-growing list of
parental failures on my part.

448
00:25:09.218 --> 00:25:10.552
Self-pity? From you?

449
00:25:10.636 --> 00:25:12.804
- [chuckles] Boy.
- [whistles] Slow down.

450
00:25:14.264 --> 00:25:15.641
Moderation? From you?

451
00:25:16.308 --> 00:25:17.309
Mm-mmm.

452
00:25:18.143 --> 00:25:19.353
What are you doing hiding up here?

453
00:25:19.937 --> 00:25:22.606
I really needed a break from all the…
showboating.

454
00:25:22.689 --> 00:25:24.149
[laughs] Yeah.

455
00:25:24.775 --> 00:25:27.819
Did I see you talking to
Samantha downstairs?

456
00:25:27.903 --> 00:25:28.904
She finally wore me down.

457
00:25:28.987 --> 00:25:30.656
- Good for you.
- It was nice actually.

458
00:25:31.782 --> 00:25:32.991
Let me tell you something though.

459
00:25:33.075 --> 00:25:35.410
She's in over her head
with that Ashe character.

460
00:25:35.494 --> 00:25:38.539
Yeah. I think we all pretty much
feel the same way.

461
00:25:40.457 --> 00:25:43.877
Even knowing everything that's wrong
between them. I still envy her.

462
00:25:43.961 --> 00:25:45.546
Sam? Really?

463
00:25:46.129 --> 00:25:47.464
The way he chases her.

464
00:25:48.090 --> 00:25:49.216
The passion.

465
00:25:50.592 --> 00:25:53.720
I don't know. I guess I just realized
it is entirely possible

466
00:25:53.804 --> 00:25:57.474
that no one will ever lust after me
like that again.

467
00:25:58.058 --> 00:25:59.059
[chuckles]

468
