473
00:26:15.033 --> 00:26:17.369
- Really?
- Yeah. I know I have.

474
00:26:19.079 --> 00:26:21.206
[gentle music playing]

475
00:26:21.290 --> 00:26:22.291
Really?

476
00:26:23.542 --> 00:26:24.543
Yep.

477
00:26:43.020 --> 00:26:44.479
Mmm.

478
00:27:03.749 --> 00:27:05.000
Oh. my God.

479
00:27:12.841 --> 00:27:13.967
[Coop moans]

480
00:27:15.135 --> 00:27:17.221
- [Mel gasps. breathes heavily]
- Oh. my God.

481
00:27:19.389 --> 00:27:21.308
[gasps. moans]

482
00:27:26.355 --> 00:27:27.814
- Let's go this way.
- [pants]

483
00:27:37.950 --> 00:27:39.993
[moans] Okay.

484
00:27:40.077 --> 00:27:41.286
Come on.

485
00:27:44.164 --> 00:27:45.874
- [Diane] Oh. my… [moans]
- [chuckles]

486
00:27:46.500 --> 00:27:47.668
[Gordy groans]

487
00:27:48.460 --> 00:27:51.839
Okay. that was… Did you know about that?

488
00:27:51.922 --> 00:27:54.007
- No.
- Come on. come on. come. on.

489
00:27:57.386 --> 00:27:58.387
[sighs]

490
00:28:00.556 --> 00:28:03.141
- I'll… I'll…
- Yeah. you… I'll…

491
00:28:03.225 --> 00:28:04.226
Coop.

492
00:28:05.602 --> 00:28:06.603
[chuckles]

493
00:28:09.982 --> 00:28:10.983
Hey.

494
00:28:12.526 --> 00:28:13.527
That's a great dress.

495
00:28:20.784 --> 00:28:22.202
You walked right past them?

496
00:28:22.286 --> 00:28:23.287
- Just like that?
- Just like that.

497
00:28:23.370 --> 00:28:24.788
They didn't even look up. They couldn't…

498
00:28:24.872 --> 00:28:25.998
They couldn't stop fighting.

499
00:28:26.081 --> 00:28:28.166
- Jesus Christ. they hate each other.
- [chuckles]

500
00:28:28.250 --> 00:28:30.335
- God was looking out for you. [chuckles]
- [exhales]

501
00:28:30.419 --> 00:28:33.005
Yeah. I never had you pegged
as a God-person.

502
00:28:33.547 --> 00:28:35.382
Oh. call it what you want.

503
00:28:35.465 --> 00:28:39.678
Religion. spirituality.
manifestation. vitamins.

504
00:28:39.761 --> 00:28:42.806
- [chuckles]
- We all need something or else…

505
00:28:42.890 --> 00:28:43.891
Or else what?

506
00:28:45.517 --> 00:28:48.353
You end up in the back of a pawn shop

507
00:28:48.437 --> 00:28:51.273
with your friend's stolen baseball card.

508
00:28:52.024 --> 00:28:53.817
"Tom Seaver." Hmm.

509
00:28:53.901 --> 00:28:56.612
This will take a little time
to authenticate.

510
00:28:56.695 --> 00:28:58.697
It's a heavily counterfeited market.

511
00:28:58.780 --> 00:29:01.074
Well. I-I kinda need this
on the faster end of things.

512
00:29:01.158 --> 00:29:03.076
Yeah. That sounds like a you problem.

513
00:29:03.160 --> 00:29:05.037
Did you ever wonder what it might be like
to be in a business

514
00:29:05.120 --> 00:29:07.247
where you give people good news
f-for a change?

515
00:29:09.124 --> 00:29:10.709
Why the sudden rush?

516
00:29:10.792 --> 00:29:14.880
I thought you were back on Wall Street
placing bets with people's pensions.

517
00:29:14.963 --> 00:29:16.507
We hardly ever see you anymore.

518
00:29:16.590 --> 00:29:20.302
Well. I tried to take your advice
vis-à-vis the blackmail situation

519
00:29:20.385 --> 00:29:23.722
and I ended up being thrown in the back
of a van with a sack on my head so…

520
00:29:24.681 --> 00:29:26.934
- And yet here you are.
- What is that supposed to mean?

521
00:29:27.559 --> 00:29:30.938
- Someone was trying to scare you.
- Well. it fucking worked. I'm scared.

522
00:29:31.855 --> 00:29:35.526
If they were serious about killing you.
they would have killed you.

523
00:29:35.609 --> 00:29:37.653
- Is that supposed to be comforting?
- Listen to me. Coop.

524
00:29:38.779 --> 00:29:42.824
The only threat you pose to these people
is right now.

525
00:29:42.908 --> 00:29:44.576
before you've done anything.

526
00:29:44.660 --> 00:29:49.122
The moment you follow through.
you become untouchable.

527
00:29:49.748 --> 00:29:51.208
This is the moment.

528
00:29:51.291 --> 00:29:52.709
It may not come again.

529
00:29:52.793 --> 00:29:54.211
Take control. Coop.

530
00:29:54.294 --> 00:29:56.713
Make yourself untouchable.

531
00:29:57.464 --> 00:29:58.590
Otherwise

532
00:30:00.175 --> 00:30:01.176
they'll own you.

533
00:30:02.219 --> 00:30:03.303
You sure about that?

534
00:30:04.263 --> 00:30:05.681
Mostly.

535
00:30:05.764 --> 00:30:08.225
I can't gamble my life on "mostly."

536
00:30:09.810 --> 00:30:12.271
What is it you think
you've been doing all this time?

537
00:30:13.105 --> 00:30:15.566
- [chuckles]
- [buzzer sounds]

538
00:30:21.154 --> 00:30:23.115
[sinister music playing]

539
00:30:36.795 --> 00:30:39.047
Hey. Rocco. Can I borrow you for a sec?

540
00:30:42.801 --> 00:30:44.219
[rock music playing]

541
00:30:59.234 --> 00:31:02.237
Hey! Fucko. What do you want from me. huh?

542
00:31:02.779 --> 00:31:05.616
What the fuck's wrong with you?
I'm on my fucking lunch break.

543
00:31:05.699 --> 00:31:07.451
Uh. sorry. man.
I thought you were someone else.

544
00:31:07.534 --> 00:31:09.077
You wanna get into it with me?

545
00:31:09.661 --> 00:31:11.288
Hey. it was an honest mistake. okay?

546
00:31:11.371 --> 00:31:14.416
You step out of that van you're gonna be
pissing sitting down for a year.

547
00:31:14.499 --> 00:31:16.502
- You hear me?
- [van driver] I hear you.

548
00:31:20.255 --> 00:31:21.715
[sighs] Sorry about that.

549
00:31:21.798 --> 00:31:23.967
Yeah. it's okay. you know?
It's better safe than sorry.

550
00:31:24.051 --> 00:31:25.385
Hey. can I keep this?

551
00:31:25.469 --> 00:31:26.470
Yeah.

552
00:31:27.346 --> 00:31:29.973
[Danny] Ellen! It's a cramp!

553
00:31:30.057 --> 00:31:32.059
[Coop chewing]

554
00:31:35.437 --> 00:31:36.438
[sighs]

555
00:31:36.522 --> 00:31:38.524
Ellen! Ellen!

556
00:31:40.025 --> 00:31:41.318
Help me!

557
00:31:50.536 --> 00:31:54.706
[Nick] Look. I'm not a crackpot. I just
think it should be a finable offense

558
00:31:54.790 --> 00:31:58.043
for the away team to wear white uniforms.
What are we even doing here?

559
00:31:58.126 --> 00:31:59.962
- It pains me to say this…
- [object clatters]

560
00:32:00.045 --> 00:32:01.338
- …but he's right.
- My man.

561
00:32:01.421 --> 00:32:03.006
[suspenseful music playing]

562
00:32:03.090 --> 00:32:04.675
If I turn on the Knicks game

563
00:32:04.758 --> 00:32:06.635
and they're playing
the world's most famous arena.

564
00:32:06.718 --> 00:32:08.804
- I want to see the core white…
- [clattering]

565
00:32:08.887 --> 00:32:09.888
Is that too much to ask?

566
00:32:09.972 --> 00:32:12.391
[Nick] And when they're away
those associations…

567
00:32:12.474 --> 00:32:13.475
[clattering continues]

568
00:32:22.734 --> 00:32:23.735
[Coop sighs]

569
00:32:24.486 --> 00:32:26.405
- Jesus. Elena.
- Careful. Coop.

570
00:32:26.488 --> 00:32:28.031
You might hurt your back.

571
00:32:28.115 --> 00:32:29.283
[grunts]

572
00:32:31.243 --> 00:32:33.662
- What are you doing here?
- I need my half of the card.

573
00:32:34.872 --> 00:32:36.748
[sighs] Wish you would've called.

574
00:32:36.832 --> 00:32:38.792
I did. And texted. a lot.

575
00:32:38.876 --> 00:32:40.377
That's probably true. Sorry.

576
00:32:41.378 --> 00:32:43.130
Why does this sound like
the beginning of an excuse?

577
00:32:43.213 --> 00:32:44.840
The card is going to take a little while.

578
00:32:44.923 --> 00:32:47.092
- [sighs] You're kidding me.
- It's a specialty item.

579
00:32:47.176 --> 00:32:48.385
My guy has to authenticate it.

580
00:32:48.468 --> 00:32:50.762
And you didn't check to see if your guy
could handle a baseball card

581
00:32:50.846 --> 00:32:53.974
before we planned an entire job around it?
We could've taken something else.

582
00:32:54.057 --> 00:32:55.684
Honestly. it never occurred to me.

583
00:32:55.767 --> 00:32:57.352
It somehow never does. Coop.

584
00:32:57.853 --> 00:32:59.062
Harsh. Okay.

585
00:32:59.146 --> 00:33:01.815
- The money is coming. All right?
- [sighs]

586
00:33:01.899 --> 00:33:03.400
Do you want a beer or something?

587
00:33:03.483 --> 00:33:06.069
- I gotta go.
- Wait. whoa. wait. Come on. stay.

588
00:33:07.154 --> 00:33:08.155
What's wrong with you?

589
00:33:08.655 --> 00:33:09.865
What? Nothing.

590
00:33:10.532 --> 00:33:13.202
I just figured maybe you'd wanna…
hang out.

591
00:33:14.661 --> 00:33:17.748
- You figured that I'd wanna hang out?
- What?

592
00:33:17.831 --> 00:33:19.666
My brother's been missing for three weeks.

593
00:33:19.750 --> 00:33:21.877
And you haven't even bothered to
check in on me.

594
00:33:21.960 --> 00:33:23.504
All you've done as far as I can see

595
00:33:23.587 --> 00:33:26.089
is let your friend lock up my money
when I needed it

596
00:33:26.173 --> 00:33:29.593
and blow me off over and over and over
when I've had jobs for us.

597
00:33:29.676 --> 00:33:31.053
Jobs that I needed.

598
00:33:31.720 --> 00:33:33.388
And you figured that
I'd just wanna hang out.

599
00:33:35.307 --> 00:33:36.600
- Elena…
- Fuck you. Coop.

600
00:33:36.683 --> 00:33:38.143
- Hey.
- No.

601
00:33:38.227 --> 00:33:41.522
If you're so lonely. why don't you
do something about it for once.

602
00:33:41.605 --> 00:33:43.899
instead of
dragging everybody down with you?

603
00:33:51.990 --> 00:33:53.075
[door opens]

604
00:33:54.785 --> 00:33:56.203
[door slams]

605
00:33:56.286 --> 00:33:57.371
[sighs]

606
00:33:57.454 --> 00:33:58.956
[downcast music playing]

607
00:34:06.713 --> 00:34:08.297
[upbeat music playing]

608
00:34:14.763 --> 00:34:16.889
[receptionist] Bailey Russell.
how may I direct your call?

609
00:34:17.516 --> 00:34:18.976
Absolutely. I'll transfer you.

610
00:34:19.685 --> 00:34:20.686
Yes. sir.

611
00:34:21.270 --> 00:34:22.271
Hi. Coop.

612
00:34:23.938 --> 00:34:25.858
- What are you doing here?
- What you won't.

613
00:34:25.940 --> 00:34:28.277
You can't bring this to Jack.
It's career suicide for you.

614
00:34:28.360 --> 00:34:30.404
Well. then I guess you'll have
nothing to worry about.

615
00:34:32.197 --> 00:34:33.282
Hey. buddy.

616
00:34:33.364 --> 00:34:34.408
Fuck me.

617
00:34:34.491 --> 00:34:37.619
Fucking fuck. every time I talk to you
it ends up costing me a half a yard.

618
00:34:37.703 --> 00:34:39.871
Look. if it means anything.
I wasn't trying to fuck you.

619
00:34:39.955 --> 00:34:41.831
[Jack] Oh. well. then. Problem solved.

620
00:34:41.915 --> 00:34:43.583
This doesn't have to
cost us anything. Jack.

621
00:34:43.667 --> 00:34:45.627
- How so?
- We can keep the investment.

622
00:34:45.710 --> 00:34:47.670
- The illegal investment?
- [Liv] Barely illegal.

623
00:34:47.754 --> 00:34:49.297
[Jack] Oh. is that gonna be your defense?

624
00:34:49.380 --> 00:34:51.466
"Were you knowingly
trading with the enemy?"

625
00:34:51.550 --> 00:34:52.551
"Barely. Your Honor."

626
00:34:52.634 --> 00:34:56.263
The enemy according to
one notoriously arbitrary administration.

627
00:34:56.346 --> 00:34:58.724
And that's if we can even take
what Coop is saying at face value.

628
00:34:58.807 --> 00:34:59.975
- You can.
- And more to the point.

629
00:35:00.058 --> 00:35:03.604
are you so sure that all the other money
we manage here is beyond reproach?

630
00:35:03.687 --> 00:35:07.024
Or is it your mandate that we start
looking into every dollar taken in here?

631
00:35:07.107 --> 00:35:10.652
Because I can assure you
that will end in tears and margin calls.

632
00:35:10.736 --> 00:35:13.739
Capital at scale is inherently corrupt.

633
00:35:14.573 --> 00:35:17.868
Is it Bailey Russell's job to be
some kind of moral arbiter

634
00:35:17.951 --> 00:35:20.495
of when that corruption is okay
and when it isn't?

635
00:35:23.248 --> 00:35:24.583
That's a very good point.

636
00:35:28.337 --> 00:35:31.256
It sounds like a point
that you've had some time to come up with.

637
00:35:34.343 --> 00:35:36.470
Coop did bring
this OFAC issue to me earlier.

638
00:35:36.553 --> 00:35:38.430
- but it didn't seem like it…
- I think we've strayed far afield…

639
00:35:38.514 --> 00:35:40.641
- Will you let me speak. please?
- I'm trying to save your job.

640
00:35:40.724 --> 00:35:41.850
I don't need you to save my job.

641
00:35:41.934 --> 00:35:43.060
- You're fired.
- Jack.

642
00:35:43.727 --> 00:35:44.728
What?

643
00:35:44.811 --> 00:35:46.688
You just told me
you've been sitting on this. How long?

644
00:35:46.772 --> 00:35:48.190
A day. a week?

645
00:35:52.986 --> 00:35:55.197
Well. then we'll give you some severance.

646
00:35:57.533 --> 00:35:58.617
Go. Now.

647
00:36:03.080 --> 00:36:04.081
[sighs]

648
00:36:08.043 --> 00:36:09.503
This was all me. Jack.

649
00:36:09.586 --> 00:36:12.130
[chuckles]
I can't really fire you. can I. Coop?

650
00:36:12.673 --> 00:36:15.259
Oh. it'll be good for her.
She's the whole package.

651
00:36:16.051 --> 00:36:18.303
Just missing one good battle scar.

652
00:36:19.847 --> 00:36:23.600
And she'll land on her feet.
outside of your big fat fucking shadow.

653
00:36:25.561 --> 00:36:26.937
- That's it?
- What?

654
00:36:27.020 --> 00:36:29.356
You're taking this a hell of a lot better
than I thought you would.

655
00:36:29.439 --> 00:36:30.482
Yeah.

656
00:36:30.983 --> 00:36:32.568
Yeah. I'm as surprised as you are.

657
00:36:34.069 --> 00:36:36.613
There was a time not long ago
I'd be lighting your ass on fire

658
00:36:36.697 --> 00:36:39.157
and making sure every fund.
from Beijing to here and back

659
00:36:39.241 --> 00:36:40.909
had your picture nailed to a wall.

660
00:36:40.993 --> 00:36:42.035
And now?

661
00:36:43.620 --> 00:36:44.997
I can't be bothered.

662
00:36:46.665 --> 00:36:47.666
Cancer's back.

663
00:36:48.834 --> 00:36:50.878
Yeah. uh. doctors found it in my prostate.

664
00:36:50.961 --> 00:36:52.838
Spread like a goddamn brush fire.

665
00:36:52.921 --> 00:36:54.006
I'm sorry. Jack.

666
00:36:54.089 --> 00:36:55.132
Yeah. me too.

667
00:36:56.925 --> 00:37:01.889
But… [sighs] …I'll tell you.
it makes you think about a lot of things.

668
00:37:02.764 --> 00:37:07.436
Especially those fights
that are worth taking on.

669
00:37:08.937 --> 00:37:10.272
So. here's what we're gonna do.

670
00:37:10.355 --> 00:37:11.732
We're gonna return the money.

671
00:37:11.815 --> 00:37:13.859
I'll handle the fallout internally.

672
00:37:13.942 --> 00:37:16.153
Nobody outside these halls has to know.

673
00:37:17.696 --> 00:37:18.989
It's better than I deserve.

674
00:37:19.072 --> 00:37:20.240
I'm not doing it for you.

675
00:37:22.659 --> 00:37:23.994
[chuckles] Maybe.

676
00:37:24.077 --> 00:37:25.370
I don't know. Maybe I am.

677
00:37:25.454 --> 00:37:26.788
Jesus. Jack. You know…

678
00:37:26.872 --> 00:37:28.123
Yeah. Hey. Coop.

679
00:37:29.333 --> 00:37:33.921
I'd imagine you have a very dangerous
and upset client on your hands.

680
00:37:34.004 --> 00:37:35.214
Are you prepared for that?

681
00:37:35.923 --> 00:37:36.924
I don't know.

682
00:37:37.007 --> 00:37:38.050
Forget your client.

683
00:37:38.133 --> 00:37:40.969
Cricket Birch
is gonna want your head on a spike.

684
00:37:41.053 --> 00:37:42.971
[sighs]

685
00:37:43.597 --> 00:37:45.057
How are you gonna plug this hole?

686
00:37:45.140 --> 00:37:46.433
Do what I always do.

687
00:37:46.934 --> 00:37:49.102
Go and find the 400 million myself.

688
00:37:49.853 --> 00:37:51.396
Ah. it'd be good for me.

689
00:37:51.480 --> 00:37:54.316
Give me a reason to
wake up and keep fighting.

690
00:37:55.025 --> 00:37:56.527
I'm really sorry. Jack.

691
00:37:56.610 --> 00:37:58.612
Yeah. I probably had it coming.

692
00:37:59.821 --> 00:38:01.949
Yeah. well. I didn't mean about the money.

693
00:38:02.032 --> 00:38:03.367
Neither did I.

694
00:38:07.079 --> 00:38:09.831
We should find some time
to play some squash.

695
00:38:09.915 --> 00:38:10.916
[chuckles]

696
00:38:12.167 --> 00:38:13.669
[pensive music playing]

697
00:38:13.752 --> 00:38:14.753
Yeah.

698
00:38:24.179 --> 00:38:26.765
[Coop] Liv was collateral damage
and I felt bad about that.

699
00:38:26.849 --> 00:38:27.975
but only to a point.

700
00:38:30.853 --> 00:38:32.563
I'd given her the chance to play the hero

701
00:38:32.646 --> 00:38:34.857
and she'd chosen to roll the dice instead.

702
00:38:35.732 --> 00:38:38.902
And while I knew she'd be okay.
it left me wondering who else in my life

703
00:38:38.986 --> 00:38:41.613
would be left holding the bag
for my actions.

704
00:38:42.906 --> 00:38:45.659
But walking away from Bailey Russell.
I felt somehow lighter.

705
00:38:45.742 --> 00:38:48.704
If Lu was to be believed.
I'd just played the only card I had.

706
00:38:48.787 --> 00:38:51.206
And while time would tell if I had
the winning hand.

707
00:38:51.290 --> 00:38:55.127
in that moment. at least I knew
I'd stopped being a helpless spectator

708
00:38:55.210 --> 00:38:56.420
to my own life.

709
00:38:57.504 --> 00:38:59.339
[construction workers shouting]

710
00:39:05.971 --> 00:39:07.472
[machinery humming]

711
00:39:10.184 --> 00:39:11.185
[humming stops]

712
00:39:30.579 --> 00:39:34.291
[Miguel speaking Spanish]

713
00:39:39.671 --> 00:39:40.672
[speaks Spanish]

714
00:39:42.758 --> 00:39:43.842
[in English] Hey.

715
00:39:47.387 --> 00:39:48.430
Hey.

716
00:39:48.514 --> 00:39:51.350
Hey. i-is… is it a holiday
I don't know about or…

717
00:39:51.433 --> 00:39:52.726
Probably.

718
00:39:52.809 --> 00:39:54.061
The Zalkins called off the job.

719
00:39:54.686 --> 00:39:56.355
Your nightmare is over. [chuckles]

720
00:39:57.022 --> 00:40:00.108
Yeah. it's a bit of a surprise
but they have to pay me out.

721
00:40:00.192 --> 00:40:02.069
And between us.
my guys are gonna be really happy

722
00:40:02.152 --> 00:40:04.947
they don't have to deal
with that lady anymore. She was…

723
00:40:05.030 --> 00:40:06.156
tricky.

724
00:40:08.116 --> 00:40:10.661
Hey. I thought you'd be happy about this.

725
00:40:11.370 --> 00:40:12.913
No. yeah. I… [stammers]

726
00:40:12.996 --> 00:40:15.874
- [chuckles] I am…
- [chuckles]

727
00:40:15.958 --> 00:40:19.378
I… I'm really sorry about
the whole driveway thing.

728
00:40:19.461 --> 00:40:22.548
I-I was taking shit out on you
that had nothing to do with you.

729
00:40:22.631 --> 00:40:23.632
Yeah?

730
00:40:24.633 --> 00:40:26.051
What kind of shit?

731
00:40:27.553 --> 00:40:28.554
Well. let's see.

732
00:40:28.637 --> 00:40:31.431
Um. I got divorced.

733
00:40:31.515 --> 00:40:33.517
Then my ex-husband
was arrested for murder.

734
00:40:33.600 --> 00:40:36.395
I lost my job because I punched my friend
at a coffee shop.

735
00:40:36.478 --> 00:40:37.980
My daughter blew off college.

736
00:40:38.063 --> 00:40:40.607
I'm getting older
at a very fucking alarming rate.

737
00:40:40.691 --> 00:40:45.696
and I'm so filled with violent rage
I'm becoming a danger to society.

738
00:40:45.779 --> 00:40:48.866
I mean. someone should just cart me off
and put me in a padded cell.

739
00:40:51.034 --> 00:40:53.078
So. what I'm hearing is you're single.

740
00:40:55.914 --> 00:40:58.041
[gasps. pants]

741
00:40:58.125 --> 00:41:00.085
[racy music playing]

742
00:41:02.546 --> 00:41:04.798
- [Miguel grunts]
- [pants]

743
00:41:17.186 --> 00:41:18.937
[both moaning]

744
00:41:19.021 --> 00:41:20.022
[mouthing words] Oh. my God.

745
00:41:20.105 --> 00:41:21.523
[moans]

746
00:41:41.168 --> 00:41:42.169
[moans]

747
00:41:45.047 --> 00:41:47.591
Um… So. I…

748
00:41:48.217 --> 00:41:50.636
- Tell me.
- No. I'm just… I'm…

749
00:41:51.345 --> 00:41:53.764
I don't know if my body works anymore.

750
00:41:53.847 --> 00:41:55.349
It may take me a while.

751
00:41:57.267 --> 00:41:58.769
[in Spanish] Everything

752
00:41:59.269 --> 00:42:00.979
with patience

753
00:42:01.772 --> 00:42:03.524
is possible.

754
00:42:03.607 --> 00:42:04.816
[panting]

755
00:42:06.443 --> 00:42:07.444
[moans]

756
00:42:38.600 --> 00:42:40.310
[watches ticking]

757
00:42:51.154 --> 00:42:52.489
[sighs]

758
00:42:55.826 --> 00:42:57.744
- [in English] Hi.
- [Tori] Hmm.

759
00:43:03.709 --> 00:43:04.918
You're glowing.

760
00:43:05.586 --> 00:43:06.587
I am?

761
00:43:10.549 --> 00:43:12.885
Probably because
I'm so happy that you're home.

762
00:43:20.309 --> 00:43:21.435
So. I met Miguel.

763
00:43:23.228 --> 00:43:24.354
You got home early?

764
00:43:24.438 --> 00:43:26.231
- Half day. Yeah.
- Oh. my God.

765
00:43:27.232 --> 00:43:28.984
- He seemed like a nice guy.
- Oh. my God.

766
00:43:29.693 --> 00:43:32.529
Is it a perm
or does his hair just like. do that?

767
00:43:33.238 --> 00:43:35.449
- Tori Cooper.
- [chuckles]

768
00:43:37.242 --> 00:43:38.368
I am. you know?

769
00:43:39.369 --> 00:43:42.289
I'm so happy to have you home
even when you torture me.

770
00:43:43.957 --> 00:43:45.167
I know. Mom.

771
00:43:45.834 --> 00:43:49.046
So. are we going to be seeing
this Miguel again?

772
00:43:49.129 --> 00:43:51.006
I think I prefer them
a little bit younger.

773
00:43:53.717 --> 00:43:54.718
Right. Yeah.

774
00:44:06.438 --> 00:44:08.982
- [sighs] Hey.
- Hey.

775
00:44:11.026 --> 00:44:13.695
So. how bad an idea is this?

776
00:44:13.779 --> 00:44:15.155
Well. we're about to find out.

777
00:44:15.822 --> 00:44:17.824
One way or the other. this ends tonight.

778
00:44:19.576 --> 00:44:21.828
I think I'm going to need you
to elaborate on that.

779
00:44:23.497 --> 00:44:24.998
I told Jack where the money is from.

780
00:44:26.458 --> 00:44:27.918
- Coop. we can't go into that house.
- Look.

781
00:44:28.001 --> 00:44:29.419
he's not gonna report it to the Feds.

782
00:44:29.503 --> 00:44:31.713
He-He… He's just gonna give it back.

783
00:44:32.464 --> 00:44:34.341
All right? And he's not even doing that

784
00:44:34.424 --> 00:44:36.385
until he finds another 400 million
to plug the hole.

785
00:44:37.010 --> 00:44:38.262
And when he does?

786
00:44:39.137 --> 00:44:41.014
When he does. Ashe will have to
find someplace else

787
00:44:41.098 --> 00:44:42.474
to invest his money without me.

788
00:44:43.892 --> 00:44:45.269
Oh. and then maybe this time

789
00:44:45.352 --> 00:44:47.437
we'll both end up
with bags over our heads. right?

790
00:44:47.521 --> 00:44:49.064
I don't think so. I…

791
00:44:49.147 --> 00:44:50.190
For what it's worth.

792
00:44:50.274 --> 00:44:53.485
I think he was pretty sincere
about not being behind that.

793
00:44:56.321 --> 00:44:58.699
[sighs]

794
00:44:59.366 --> 00:45:00.576
You wanna go home?

795
00:45:01.410 --> 00:45:02.494
This is my mess.

796
00:45:03.328 --> 00:45:04.538
You don't need to be here.

797
00:45:06.540 --> 00:45:07.541
[clicks tongue]

798
00:45:08.083 --> 00:45:09.626
I'm your business manager. Coop.

799
00:45:10.961 --> 00:45:12.379
Let's go take care of business.

800
00:45:13.755 --> 00:45:15.549
- You sure?
- No.

801
00:45:16.925 --> 00:45:19.011
It's just four guys
sitting around talking. right?

802
00:45:20.262 --> 00:45:21.263
All good.

803
00:45:22.598 --> 00:45:23.599
[Coop] We'll be fine.

804
00:45:23.682 --> 00:45:25.475
- [chuckles]
- What?

805
00:45:26.518 --> 00:45:29.062
I was just thinking about all
the other times you've said that.

806
00:45:29.855 --> 00:45:31.690
I'm bound to be right one of these days.

807
00:45:32.274 --> 00:45:34.318
[rock music playing]

808
00:45:34.401 --> 00:45:36.403
Gentlemen. right on time.

809
00:45:36.486 --> 00:45:38.197
- Yes. sir!
- You're in a good mood.

810
00:45:38.280 --> 00:45:39.948
- Hey. happiness is a choice. right?
- Hey.

811
00:45:40.032 --> 00:45:42.242
- A mindset.
- Exactly.

812
00:45:42.326 --> 00:45:43.535
You guys got some catching up to do.

813
00:45:43.619 --> 00:45:45.954
Food's in the dining room.
Make yourselves a plate.

814
00:45:46.038 --> 00:45:47.289
Meet me in the living room.

815
00:45:49.208 --> 00:45:50.334
Let's eat.

816
00:45:54.671 --> 00:45:56.131
Where'd all the staff go?

817
00:45:56.215 --> 00:45:57.799
He sent them home.

818
00:45:57.883 --> 00:46:00.135
Said he wanted it to be just us tonight.

819
00:46:00.844 --> 00:46:02.554
Uh. he's a mess.

820
00:46:03.305 --> 00:46:05.557
- [Ashe humming]
- Seems pretty happy.

821
00:46:07.059 --> 00:46:08.060
Whoo!

822
00:46:08.644 --> 00:46:11.480
Well. he just switched
from coke to ketamine. so…

823
00:46:12.731 --> 00:46:15.943
Buckle up. boys. It's gonna get bumpy.

824
00:46:16.026 --> 00:46:18.737
[Ashe grunts] Hey. You guys want in?

825
00:46:19.780 --> 00:46:21.573
I got powder if you don't like needles.

826
00:46:21.657 --> 00:46:23.742
Oh. you don't know what you're missing.

827
00:46:23.825 --> 00:46:25.619
At least make yourselves some drinks.

828
00:46:25.702 --> 00:46:27.412
[Nick] I'm good with what I got.

829
00:46:27.496 --> 00:46:28.580
Yeah. man. Yeah.

830
00:46:28.664 --> 00:46:30.958
So. uh. this whole thing with Sam…

831
00:46:31.041 --> 00:46:33.502
Oh. fuck that Sam. Jesus Christ.

832
00:46:33.585 --> 00:46:35.420
There's plenty where that came from.

833
00:46:35.504 --> 00:46:38.382
But good friends. that's the good stuff.

834
00:46:38.465 --> 00:46:40.008
You know. I was worried
that Westmont Village

835
00:46:40.092 --> 00:46:41.885
was gonna be
one of those clichéd communities

836
00:46:41.969 --> 00:46:44.680
where everyone just watches each other.

837
00:46:44.763 --> 00:46:46.431
and sees who has the biggest house.

838
00:46:46.515 --> 00:46:48.517
and the most expensive car
and the best jewelry.

839
00:46:48.600 --> 00:46:51.019
Yeah. well. if it is. you win.

840
00:46:51.103 --> 00:46:52.646
[laughs]

841
00:46:52.729 --> 00:46:55.148
I will admit.
I don't mind rising above the game.

842
00:46:55.232 --> 00:46:57.609
But I have to say.
you all are good people. You are.

843
00:46:57.693 --> 00:47:01.029
Y-You welcomed Delilah and me
into your little circle with open arms.

844
00:47:01.113 --> 00:47:03.699
And I know it's not been very long
but… [sniffs]

845
00:47:04.241 --> 00:47:06.410
…I am honored to call you all my friends.

846
00:47:07.244 --> 00:47:09.371
[Nick] Bonded in friendship and business.

847
00:47:09.454 --> 00:47:10.622
[Ashe] Amen.

848
00:47:10.706 --> 00:47:12.833
Mmm. [gulps]

849
00:47:12.916 --> 00:47:16.795
Hey. which reminds me to give you
guys a little friendly heads-up.

850
00:47:16.879 --> 00:47:19.882
The lawyers are gonna have to
submit financials to my bank.

851
00:47:19.965 --> 00:47:21.967
We need to set up a revolving credit line

852
00:47:22.050 --> 00:47:25.179
so that we can start cash flowing
to the expansion team.

853
00:47:25.262 --> 00:47:29.391
So. I'm gonna need you
to clean up those monies

854
00:47:29.474 --> 00:47:31.560
you're moving through the business ASAP.

855
00:47:31.643 --> 00:47:33.312
Uh. what-what monies?

856
00:47:33.395 --> 00:47:34.855
Oh. hey. No judgment.

857
00:47:34.938 --> 00:47:36.899
What's a little cash scrubbing
between friends. huh?

858
00:47:36.982 --> 00:47:38.734
It's a couple hundred thousand.
we've all been there.

859
00:47:38.817 --> 00:47:40.068
Um. I haven't.

860
00:47:41.028 --> 00:47:42.654
The fuck's he talking about?

861
00:47:43.447 --> 00:47:45.574
Whoa. Oh. I'm sorry. I thought…

862
00:47:47.618 --> 00:47:48.619
He didn't know?

863
00:47:50.662 --> 00:47:51.955
- Well. shit.
- Look. this…

864
00:47:52.039 --> 00:47:53.790
this is all just a misunderstanding.

865
00:47:53.874 --> 00:47:55.292
Then why don't you explain it to me?

866
00:47:55.375 --> 00:47:59.004
Yeah. 600K in magic receivables
all involving LLCs tied to you

867
00:47:59.588 --> 00:48:02.466
- doesn't sound like a misunderstanding.
- Barney. start talking.

868
00:48:02.549 --> 00:48:04.801
Wait a minute. wait a minute.
If you didn't do this for Nick…

869
00:48:05.802 --> 00:48:07.262
who'd you cut that check to?

870
00:48:10.307 --> 00:48:12.017
- Oh. [chuckles]
- Shut up. Ashe.

871
00:48:12.100 --> 00:48:14.603
Coop! Wait. what the fuck? Both of you?

872
00:48:14.686 --> 00:48:16.688
You were running money through my gym?

873
00:48:16.772 --> 00:48:18.941
It was… Look.
it was just a paper shuffle. Nick. Okay?

874
00:48:19.024 --> 00:48:20.692
You know. we were short on receivables.

875
00:48:20.776 --> 00:48:22.903
Coop had some cash
that he wanted to keep off of the books.

876
00:48:23.695 --> 00:48:26.281
It was a one-time transaction.
It just killed two birds with one stone.

877
00:48:26.365 --> 00:48:27.991
Barney was trying to help me out
with a tax thing

878
00:48:28.075 --> 00:48:30.160
after Bailey Russell went sideways.
It's just…

879
00:48:30.244 --> 00:48:31.537
Why didn't you ask me?

880
00:48:31.620 --> 00:48:32.871
I would've helped you if you needed.

881
00:48:32.955 --> 00:48:35.207
I didn't tell you because it was nothing.
It's a quick pass-through.

882
00:48:35.290 --> 00:48:36.416
Wait. wait.

883
00:48:36.500 --> 00:48:39.378
Is… Is this why
you didn't want me to bring Ashe in?

884
00:48:39.461 --> 00:48:41.547
No. That… No. that's completely separate.

885
00:48:41.630 --> 00:48:45.384
Oh. so. you were gonna cost me
a major expansion just to cover your ass?

886
00:48:45.467 --> 00:48:46.802
The fuck. Barney?

887
00:48:47.928 --> 00:48:49.096
Shit. man.

888
00:48:49.972 --> 00:48:52.850
- Shit. Oh. my God.
- [Ashe] Not a good look. guys.

889
00:48:53.433 --> 00:48:55.602
Hey. We're all friends here. Come on.

890
00:48:56.103 --> 00:48:57.938
- Let's dial it down a notch.
- [Nick] Bro.

891
00:48:58.021 --> 00:48:59.523
We're all about to make
a lot of money together.

892
00:49:01.650 --> 00:49:02.651
Right.

893
00:49:05.195 --> 00:49:06.196
No.

894
00:49:07.239 --> 00:49:08.615
No. we're not.

895
00:49:10.826 --> 00:49:11.827
We're done.

896
00:49:11.910 --> 00:49:13.370
[chuckles] Wh…

897
00:49:14.037 --> 00:49:16.665
- Wh-What does that mean?
- [Barney] Is now the right time. Coop?

898
00:49:16.748 --> 00:49:18.250
Bailey Russell's gonna
return the funds to you.

899
00:49:18.333 --> 00:49:20.878
They know it's your money
and they know you're on the OFAC list.

900
00:49:20.961 --> 00:49:22.671
[ominous music playing]

901
00:49:24.464 --> 00:49:25.716
And how do they know that?

902
00:49:25.799 --> 00:49:27.718
Because I told them.

903
00:49:28.302 --> 00:49:29.511
Fuck me.

904
00:49:31.513 --> 00:49:32.931
You pathetic little man.

905
00:49:34.141 --> 00:49:36.476
I fucking paved your way
back into the hedge fund world

906
00:49:36.560 --> 00:49:37.936
on a goddamn yellow brick road.

907
00:49:38.020 --> 00:49:39.855
And you fucking blow it up?

908
00:49:41.815 --> 00:49:42.983
You're gonna fix it. Coop.

909
00:49:43.066 --> 00:49:44.151
Well. I can't.

910
00:49:46.320 --> 00:49:48.488
So. thank you for this.

911
00:49:48.572 --> 00:49:49.907
- I'll see myself out.
- [Ashe] No. Hey.

912
00:49:49.990 --> 00:49:51.950
Hey. You're gonna fix it. Coop!

913
00:49:52.451 --> 00:49:53.744
You're gonna fix it!

914
00:49:54.411 --> 00:49:55.662
You think you can fuck me like that?

915
00:49:55.746 --> 00:49:58.165
I know where you live.
I know where your family lives.

916
00:49:58.248 --> 00:50:00.542
[ominous music continues]

917
00:50:00.626 --> 00:50:03.295
- What the fuck did you just say?
- What? You think there's rules here?

918
00:50:03.378 --> 00:50:04.379
Wake up!

919
00:50:04.922 --> 00:50:07.466
You fuck with my livelihood.
there will be consequences.

920
00:50:07.549 --> 00:50:08.926
You fucking kidding me? Fuck you.

921
00:50:09.009 --> 00:50:10.469
I'll fucking kill you.

922
00:50:10.552 --> 00:50:12.137
- You understand me?
- [Barney] No. Coop!

923
00:50:12.221 --> 00:50:13.430
- I'll fucking kill you.
- No!

924
00:50:13.514 --> 00:50:14.640
Motherfucker. Threaten my family?

925
00:50:14.723 --> 00:50:17.434
- Motherfucker. [grunts]
- You're gonna fucking kill me?

926
00:50:17.518 --> 00:50:19.686
- You're gonna kill me?
- Please. Coop.

927
00:50:19.770 --> 00:50:21.522
[clamoring]

928
00:50:22.397 --> 00:50:24.191
- Come on.
- Whoa! Hey!

929
00:50:24.274 --> 00:50:26.109
- W-Whoa. hey!
- [Nick] A fucking gun?

930
00:50:26.193 --> 00:50:27.486
[Ashe] Kill me.

931
00:50:28.403 --> 00:50:30.614
You said you were gonna kill me. Kill me.

932
00:50:32.824 --> 00:50:34.409
You have no idea who you're fucking with.

933
00:50:34.493 --> 00:50:37.704
Come on. Ashe.
Hey. let's all just calm the fuck down.

934
00:50:38.288 --> 00:50:40.624
- [chuckles] I'm calm.
- Okay.

935
00:50:40.707 --> 00:50:42.876
I'm cool as a fucking cucumber. [laughs]

936
00:50:42.960 --> 00:50:44.878
[laughing]

937
00:50:46.129 --> 00:50:47.631
Back off. Superstar.

938
00:50:49.132 --> 00:50:50.717
[Nick] You don't wanna do this. man.

939
00:50:51.510 --> 00:50:53.345
Come on. we're all having a bad night.
Like you said.

940
00:50:53.428 --> 00:50:56.265
- let's just take it down a notch.
- Kindly shut the fuck up. Nick.

941
00:50:58.851 --> 00:51:00.435
I thought you were my friend.

942
00:51:01.436 --> 00:51:03.355
- Did you really?
- Not helping. Coop.

943
00:51:03.438 --> 00:51:04.523
He threatened my family. Are…

944
00:51:04.606 --> 00:51:06.817
- [gunshot]
- [screams] Fuck!

945
00:51:06.900 --> 00:51:08.277
Oh. shit.

946
00:51:08.360 --> 00:51:10.028
- [Coop] Hey. Come on.
- [Barney] Get him. Nick!

947
00:51:10.112 --> 00:51:11.488
[clamoring]

948
00:51:11.572 --> 00:51:13.949
Get the gun! Get the gun!

949
00:51:14.992 --> 00:51:16.243
- Whoa. whoa. whoa.
- [Barney] Nick.

950
00:51:16.326 --> 00:51:17.786
[grunting]

951
00:51:17.870 --> 00:51:19.913
- [gunshot]
- [grunting]

952
00:51:20.873 --> 00:51:23.584
[Barney] Stop. Please. Not at me.
Not at me. Not at me.

953
00:51:25.627 --> 00:51:26.837
[groans]

954
00:51:26.920 --> 00:51:28.005
[grunts] Ow!

955
00:51:30.299 --> 00:51:31.300
[grunts]

956
00:51:33.177 --> 00:51:35.262
- [yells]
- Oh. shit!

957
00:51:35.345 --> 00:51:36.847
Fuck you! [shouts]

958
00:51:38.682 --> 00:51:40.017
You little bitches!

959
00:51:40.100 --> 00:51:41.393
[Coop] Oh. my God!

960
00:51:43.187 --> 00:51:44.605
[music ends]

961
00:52:22.392 --> 00:52:24.394
[sighs]

962
00:52:26.021 --> 00:52:27.022
He's dead.

963
00:52:28.398 --> 00:52:30.567
[fire alarm ringing]
